                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18400406-1269-offence-1 t18400406-name-1363"></join>Thomas Cooper</persName>, from his person; and that he had been before convicted of felony.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1364" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1364" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1364" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1364" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS COOPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Chapel-street, Pentonville. On the evening</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184004060196"></xptr>
               <p>of the 8th of April I was in Little Britain—I received information, turned, and saw the prisoner, and accused him of having stolen my handkerchief—he denied it—he was searched in my presence, and this handkerchief found on him—it is mine, and was safe a quarter of an hour before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did not a gentleman cross the road, and say, "You have got a gentleman's handkerchief?" then you ran across, and said, "Yes, that is my handkerchief." it was found on the stones. <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> It was taken from under your waistcoat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1365" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1365" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1365" type="surname" value="COLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1365" type="given" value="WELCOME"></interp>WELCOME COLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I was walking opposite the prosecutor. I saw the prisoner and another walking behind the prosecutor—I saw the prisoner raise the tail of his coat, and take the handkerchief—I crossed, and told the prosecutor—I hastened after the prisoner, and took the handkerchief from under his waistcoat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1366" type="witnessName">
